data.enText: the mark ( : ) used to introduce a list, a summary, an explanation, etc. or before reporting what sb has said
the main part of the large intestine (= part of the bowels )

tr: the part of the large intestine between the cecum and the rectum
it extracts moisture from food residues before they are excreted
a punctuation mark (:) used after a word introducing a series or an example or an explanation (or after the salutation of a business letter)
the basic unit of money in Costa Rica
the basic unit of money in El Salvador

value.def: A colon is the punctuation mark : which you can use in several ways. For example, you can put it before a list of things or before reported speech.
Your colon is the part of your intestine above your rectum.
